  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What qualification do you need for a nursing job?",
  "response": "The qualifications needed for a nursing job can vary depending on the country, the specific role, and the healthcare setting. However, some general requirements include:\n\n1. **Educational Requirements:**\n   - **Registered Nurse (RN):** Typically requires a Bachelor of Science in Nursing (BSN) or an Associate Degree in Nursing (ADN). Some places may still accept a diploma from an approved nursing program.\n   - **Licensed Practical/Vocational Nurse (LPN/LVN):** Generally requires a diploma or certificate from an accredited practical nursing program.\n   - **Advanced Practice Registered Nurse (APRN):** Requires a Master's of Science in Nursing (MSN) or Doctor of Nursing Practice (DNP), depending on the specialization (e.g., Nurse Practitioner, Clinical Nurse Specialist).\n\n2. **Licensure:**\n   - Nurses must pass the National Council Licensure Examination (NCLEX-RN for registered nurses or NCLEX-PN for practical/vocational nurses) to obtain a nursing license.\n   - APRNs often need additional certification in their specialty area.\n\n3. **Certification and Continuing Education:**\n   - While not always mandatory, additional certification in specialties (e.g., pediatrics, oncology, emergency nursing) is often preferred and sometimes required.\n   - Nurses are typically required to complete continuing education credits to maintain their licenses and stay updated on medical knowledge and practices.\n\n4. **Skills and Competencies:**\n   - Strong communication and interpersonal skills.\n   - Compassionate and patient-focused attitude.\n   - Ability to work in high-stress environments and make critical decisions.\n   - Competency in performing clinical tasks and using medical technologies.\n\n5. **Background Check and Health Requirements:**\n   - A clean background check and up-to-date immunizations and health screenings usually required.\n\n6. **Experience:**\n   - Some positions require a certain amount of clinical experience or may specify particular areas of expertise.\n\nIt's important for prospective nurses to check the specific requirements in their region or by the healthcare institutions where they wish to work, as there can be significant variations.",
